item.title: My university
item.dc:creator: @davidi2 Davidi2
item.description:
@davidi2 wrote:

[quote=“xx matty xx, post:5, topic:409075”][quote author=Davidi2 link=topic=510358.msg3703790#msg3703790 date=1312913310]
Have fun with that

Whereas I am provided two free years of uni here for starting while still in high school 8) (or college for you international fags)
[/quote]what how, I thought university cost like 20k in the US?[/quote]It’s a special program for my state called Running Start. If you have a certain GPA and meet other ‘academic excellence’ standards, you can go to a College/Uni(international fags) and get dual credits (if you take say a quarter of Calculus at the Uni, you get a full years worth of high school credit AND the normal college credit) toward your diploma/degree. You can start it Junior year of HS if you meet the criteria. Basically you can get a Bachelors at the same time you get your Highschool diploma.

I probably didn’t explain it very well, so http://www.k12.wa.us/SecondaryEducation/CareerCollegeReadiness/RunningStart.aspx

Read full topic
